Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodianpottery transport amphora, with gradual curve. Clay near fine buff-brown. Circular stamp with rose symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Euphranor. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0125.36. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0724)
